<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">For starters I think alot of you ppl need to mature to the lvl of a good argument. With that being said I don't think this topic is an argument but I do honestly believe alot of ppl have no real clue about some things, or for the most part either side of this issue.

For starters here's my Flame:
Anyone thinking this is a "Loot" thing needs a "boot to tha head" end of story on that clueless PoV.

"But I feel that no guild should say you have to be here if your online, or else. Thats not what a guild is about."
If a guild lists this as part of their core principals then by God you better follow it. If you don't follow this principal then it's obvious you either haven't joined this guild or you don't really know what you want out of the game. -End

What everyone in this thread has to realize is there are different reasons for each one of us playing this game. And we need to respect both sides of the fence(which some of you are having trouble doing, who are you to decide who's a real cleric and who isn't? you're nobody, live with it) No one side is more right or more wrong than the other. So get over yourself.

My guild? We are a raid guild formed from the ground up with that in mind. We raid for the majority of the week whether it's scheduled or not which is funny. We're into Overkill and it's not the Phat L3wt that drives ppl it's the comradery amongst the guild. We all like seeing ppl get new things. We all like seeing new places, doing harder things, and there's nothing like pulling off the near impossible and making it look easy. It's one of the best feelings you'll ever have in this game whether there's 3 ppl in your group or 300 it's still the same feeling.

Belittling both sides of this argument is pointless, cause they're both right and they're both wrong. If you want to sit in Oasis and buff newbies and Res the less fortunate, hey, more power to ya. If someone gets their thrills out of slaying some Velious baddie, hey, more power to ya. Neither of which is a crime. And if you think that all those in raid guilds are nothing but lootwhores and such then you're quite clueless. When my guild goes to Fear it's funny how we'll have more ppl there than you would think and hey! more clerics than you can shake a stick at, yeah...we're there for the loot allright  ;)

So wisen up, lighten up and accept the fact that there's different ways to play, none of which are inherently wrong(no stupid KS, PK arguments either).


Sini</TEXTAREA>
